    <key>CBReleaseWhatsNew</key>
    <string>Account swap no longer asks you to re-login when it just hit a transient OAuth rate limit or network blip — the swap quietly defers and you can retry.
A polished failure card now explains exactly what went wrong (rate-limited, busy, transient, or actually needs re-login), with a one-click Retry or Re-login button.
Footer drops the Briefing button; the Daily Briefing window stays one ⌥X hotkey away.</string>
    <key>CBReleaseHotfixes</key>
    <string>Fixed swap failing with a misleading "credentials need login again" whenever OAuth refresh hit a 429 or transient error.
Fixed potential backup credential loss when a Keychain ACL migration's re-add step transiently failed.
Fixed swap occasionally failing on a partial ~/.claude.json read while Claude Code was rewriting it.
Fixed swap hanging indefinitely if another csw operation held the file lock (now times out after 30s with a clear message).</string>
